With its 1200 years of deep-rooted history, Hamburg is known as the b Door to the World ’thanks to its nearly 100 consulates.
The natural lakes, nature parks and bridges take place in the city between Alster and Elbe rivers. With the world's largest container port city, you can start your journey first on the Rathausmarkt street and visit the Hamburg Town Hall in the area.
